<div id="review_1058483181" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1058483181" />
    <a title="Sean O" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5984690-sean-o"><img alt="Sean O" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1430246441p2/5984690.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1058483181?book_show_action=true">Sep 18, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sean O" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sean O" href="/user/show/5984690-sean-o">Sean O</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/19014812-the-glory-and-the-dream">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5984690-sean-o?shelf=5star">5star</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1058483181" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5324740150200014626">I&apos;m not sure it&apos;s possible to adequately review a 1300+ page narrative history of the middle of the 20th Century. So I&apos;m not sure I&apos;m going to try.<br/><br/>This book however is a beautiful skeleton. <br/><br/>On it I will hang Atkinson&apos;s &quot;Liberation&quot; trilogy, Halberstam&apos;s &quot;The Fifties,&quot; &quot;The Children,&quot; and &quot;The Best and the Brightest,&quot; &quot;All the King&apos;s Men,&quot; and &quot;All the President&apos;s Men.&quot; <br/><br/>If you want to know what happened in America from 1932 to 1972, this is the place to start.</span>
  <span id="freeText5324740150200014626" style="display:none">I'm not sure it's possible to adequately review a 1300+ page narrative history of the middle of the 20th Century. So I'm not sure I'm going to try.<br /><br />This book however is a beautiful skeleton. <br /><br />On it I will hang Atkinson's "Liberation" trilogy, Halberstam's "The Fifties," "The Children," and "The Best and the Brightest," "All the King's Men," and "All the President's Men." <br /><br />If you want to know what happened in America from 1932 to 1972, this is the place to start.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5324740150200014626" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


