<div id="review_3243137499" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3243137499" />
    <a title="Edward Benyas" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/31490637-edward-benyas"><img alt="Edward Benyas" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3243137499?book_show_action=true">May 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Edward Benyas" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Edward Benyas" href="/user/show/31490637-edward-benyas">Edward Benyas</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780316544962" href="/book/show/1340152.The_Glory_and_the_Dream">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3243137499" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17181308681721493100">This is one of the best books I have ever read, and Manchester is definitely one of my favorite authors. I&apos;ve read his 3-volume seminal biography of Churchill, which is terrific, and also Death of a President, which is also excellent. The Glory and the Dream is even better. In its 1600 pages I was never bored and never wanted to take a break and start another book. Manchester covers everything that is important in this crucial 40-year period of American history: Presidents, Congress, the Supreme</span>
  <span id="freeText17181308681721493100" style="display:none">This is one of the best books I have ever read, and Manchester is definitely one of my favorite authors. I've read his 3-volume seminal biography of Churchill, which is terrific, and also Death of a President, which is also excellent. The Glory and the Dream is even better. In its 1600 pages I was never bored and never wanted to take a break and start another book. Manchester covers everything that is important in this crucial 40-year period of American history: Presidents, Congress, the Supreme Court, foreign affairs, cultural history, the economy, protest movements, and of course the Depression, WWII, Korea, McCarthyism, Vietnam and Watergate, all with great detail. And it is amazing how so much that he describes has been repeated since. His portrayal of McCarthy is eerily similar to Trump. Racial tensions of the 60's are front and center again today. I heartily recommend it to any Americans interested in our recent past.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17181308681721493100" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

