<div id="review_1496232774" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1496232774" />
    <a title="Andrew Breza" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3477133-andrew-breza"><img alt="Andrew Breza" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1554747743p2/3477133.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1496232774?book_show_action=true">Sep 17, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Andrew Breza" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Andrew Breza" href="/user/show/3477133-andrew-breza">Andrew Breza</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1496232774" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2578850993694694499">Too many books about American history either uncritically praise our nation or obsess over its flaws. Manchester finds a third path. In telling the story of the country through such a turbulent period, he illustrates both America&apos;s potential and times when we have fallen short. Any book of this length requires dedication to finish, but Glory and the Dream is worth the effort.</span>
  <span id="freeText2578850993694694499" style="display:none">Too many books about American history either uncritically praise our nation or obsess over its flaws. Manchester finds a third path. In telling the story of the country through such a turbulent period, he illustrates both America's potential and times when we have fallen short. Any book of this length requires dedication to finish, but Glory and the Dream is worth the effort.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2578850993694694499" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


